ut 1385","1419":"1419","about 1340":"about 1340","Scotland":"Scotland","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Thompson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: patronymic from the Middle English personal name <i>T(h)om(me)</i> (see   Thom  ) + <i>-son</i> ‘son of <i>Tom</i>’.   Thomson   is usually the Scottish form, that with the intrusive <i>-p-</i> being English. Both forms are common in Ireland. The surname <i>Thompson</i> is also very common among African Americans.","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Thomsen   and of its Swedish cognate <b>Thomsson</b>. Compare   Thomson  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Thomson","meanings":["Scottish, English and northern Irish: variant of   Thompson  .","Scottish: sometimes an Anglicized form of Gaelic <i>McThomas</i>; see   McTavish  ,   McComish  .","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Thomsen  . Compare   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Thom","meanings":["Scottish and English: from the Middle English personal name <i>T(h)om(me)</i>, a pet form of   Thomas  . In Scotland, <i>Thom</i> is also an Anglicized form of Gaelic <i>Mac Thom</i>, see   McComb  .","German: from the personal name <i>Thom</i>, a pet form of   Thomas  . This surname is also found in France.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 譚, see   Tan   1."]},{"name":"Tomson","meanings":["English: variant of   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Thompsom","meanings":["Altered form of   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Tompson","meanings":["English: variant of   Thompson  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Thompson II was born in 1358, in Scotland, his father, William Thompson I, was 38 and his mother, Anne Pennington, was 38. He married Isabella Sudbury about 1379, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1419, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1358–1419":"1358–1419","1340–1425":"1340–1425","1354–1354":"1354–1354","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1360–Female":"1360–Surnud","1361–Female":"1361–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1364–1419":"1364–1419","1364–Male":"1364–Surnud","1359–Female":"1359–Surnud","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1382–Male":"1382–Surnud","1385–1425":"1385–1425","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1359":"1359","1425":"1425","1358":"1358","1355":"1355","1354":"1354","1320":"1320","1364":"1364","about 1379":"umbes 1379","about 1385":"umbes 1385","1419":"1419","about 1340":"umbes 1340","Scotland":"Scotland","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1358–1419":"1358–1419","1340–1425":"1340–1425","1354–1354":"1354–1354","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1360–Female":"1360–Kuollut","1361–Female":"1361–Kuollut","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1364–1419":"1364–1419","1364–Male":"1364–Kuollut","1359–Female":"1359–Kuollut","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1382–Male":"1382–Kuollut","1385–1425":"1385–1425","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1320–Female":"1320–Kuollut","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1359":"1359","1425":"1425","1358":